{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1f400e1-8352-4867-888a-b9d4c83fd491","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you need to make one change in your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nMSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is sufficient.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Run tests with `dotnet test` as before (it works with both runners).\n- CLI output format changes slightly.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may behave differently — review any custom runsettings you use.\n- If you use `dotnet test --filter`, the filter syntax remains the same.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27ba0b76-70e3-41ab-b42f-49c7d3e2c42d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, so I can answer directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"7C2A:1E7C59:137A9C2:15EFABF:69F93FD2"},"id":"ae074be8-9c39-4ba7-8c00-5d52887bfe4d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:54:49.277Z","parentId":"fce002c8-bf45-4ada-8d40-db5fbf925bb6"}
